etymologies: late 15th century (in an earlier sense). As noun from Middle French saturnelles, saturnales, plural noun (French saturnales) ancient Roman festival of Saturn, (in extended use) bout of revelry, orgy from classical Latin Sāturnālia

definitions: Relating to or affected by the supposed influence of the planet Saturn; designating this influence. Compare "saturnine".
Of or relating to the god Saturn; especially designating the ancient Roman Saturnalia. Compare saturnial.
Of or relating to the planet Saturn; resembling that of the planet Saturn.
